<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-4288] GroovyScriptEngine can&apos;t refresh class from url other than file</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-4288</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;the class GroovyScriptEngine loaded from a url other than file will never be updated. I made a patch for it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;exam:&lt;br/&gt;
gse = new groovy.util.GroovyScriptEngine(new String[] &lt;/p&gt;
{ &quot;scripts&quot;,
				&quot;http://localhost/&quot; }
&lt;p&gt;);&lt;br/&gt;
gse.getConfig().setMinimumRecompilationInterval(0);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;the class from &lt;a href=&quot;http://localhost/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://localhost/&lt;/a&gt; will never refresh.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I found this when made a URL type for JDBC.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
